The remains of Roland Kelechi Uwazurike will be laid to rest on Saturday January 25, 2020, at Umunakanu-Owere, Ehime-Mbano Local Government Area, Imo State. Requiem mass holds same day at St. Theresaâ€™s Catholic Church, Umunakanu-Owere, at 11 am. Uwazuruike died in Abuja on December 21, 2019, after a brief illness at the age of 48. He is survived by Cindy, wife; three children, including Enyioma, Ezinwa and Kevin; eight siblings, among whom are Professors C. N. Uwazurike and Chudi Uwazurike, Goddy Uwazurike, former president of Aka Ikenga, Dr. John and Justina,  Chukwu and Johnkay, as well as Dr. Evelyn Nwadinobi, Dr. Josie Uwazurike, Eziada Lizzy, Ijeoma Ochulo, aunts, cousins,  nieces and nephews.